NAME
generate_report.sh - generate git commit reports for specified time periods

SYNOPSIS
generate_report.sh [PERIOD | DATE [END_DATE]]

DESCRIPTION
Generate a formatted markdown table of git commits grouped by date for
the current repository. The script filters commits by the current git
user and excludes merge commits.

       Output format includes:
       - Author name
       - Date-grouped commit tables with:
         * Short commit ID (7 characters)
         * Commit message

ARGUMENTS
PERIOD
Predefined time period (see PERIODS section)

       DATE
              Specific date in YYYY-MM-DD format
              If only DATE is provided, generates report for that single day

       END_DATE
              Optional end date in YYYY-MM-DD format
              When provided with DATE, generates report for the date range

PERIODS
today
Current day (00:00:00 to now)

       yesterday
              Previous day (yesterday 00:00:00 to today 00:00:00)

       thisweek
              Current week from Monday to today

       lastweek
              Previous week from Monday to Sunday

       thismonth
              Current month from 1st to today

       lastmonth
              Previous month (1st to last day)

OPTIONS
No options are available. The script uses positional arguments only.

EXAMPLES
Generate report for today:
$ generate_report.sh
$ generate_report.sh today

       Generate report for yesterday:
              $ generate_report.sh yesterday

       Generate report for current week:
              $ generate_report.sh thisweek

       Generate report for last month:
              $ generate_report.sh lastmonth

       Generate report for specific date:
              $ generate_report.sh 2025-12-24

       Generate report for date range:
              $ generate_report.sh 2025-12-20 2025-12-24

OUTPUT FORMAT
The output is in markdown format:

              - Author: <git user name>

              - Date: <YYYY-MM-DD>

              | Commit ID | Message |
              | :-------- | :------ |
              | abc1234   | feat: add new feature |
              | def5678   | fix: bug fix |

       Multiple dates are separated by blank lines with their own tables.

ENVIRONMENT
The script requires: - Git repository (must be run within a git repository) - macOS date command (uses -j and -v flags) - Git user.name configuration

EXIT STATUS
0 Success

       1      Invalid date parameter or format error

NOTES - The script uses macOS-specific date command syntax - For Linux/GNU systems, the date calculations may need modification - Only commits by the current git user are included - Merge commits are automatically excluded (--no-merges) - Time ranges are inclusive of start date, exclusive of end date

SEE ALSO
git-log(1), date(1)

BUGS
Date calculations rely on macOS date command. For portability to
Linux systems, consider using GNU date (gdate) or alternative
date calculation methods.

